1. pandas.head()

2. pandas.tail()

3. pandas.info()

4. pandas.dtypes

5. pandas.shape()

6. pandas.size()

7. pandas.describe() - statistical summary 

8. pandas.sample() - Sample method allows you to select values randomly from a Series or DataFrame. 

9. pandas.isnull() - dentifying Missing Values Isnull

10. pandas.Isna().any() - isna function returns a dataframe filled with boolean values with true indicating missing values.

11. pandas.isnull().sum() - Identifying Missing Values Sum

12. pandas.nunique() - Nunique counts the number of unique entries over columns or rows.

13. pandas.index() - given element from the start of the list and returns the lowest index where the element appears.

14. pandas.columns() - give alll columns .

15. pandas.Memory_usage() - returns how much memory each column uses in bytes .

16. pandas.nsmallest() and pandas.nlargest()

17. pandas.Loc and pandas.iloc 

18. pandas.groupby : pandas groupby function is a great tool in exploring the data


19. pandas.sor_index() method ::: Using the sort_index() method, by passing the axis arguments and the order of sorting, DataFrame can be sorted

20. pandas.Dropna() ::: The dropna () function is used to remove a row or a column from a dataframe which has a NaN or no values in it.

21. pandas.query() :: filter a dataframe based on a condition or apply a mask to get certain values. One easy way to filter a dataframe is query function.

22. pandas.insert() ::  we want to add a new column to a dataframe, it is added at the end by default. However, pandas offers the option to add the new column in any position using insert function.


23. pandas.read_csv()

24. pandas.astype() - Type Conversion of Data columns

25. pandas.to_datetime() - to_datetime() converts a Python object to datetime format. 

26. pandas.value_counts() - value_counts() returns a Pandas Series containing the counts of unique values. 

27. pandas.drop_duplicates() - drop_duplicates() returns a Pandas DataFrame with duplicate rows removed. 

28. pandas.merge() - is used to merge 2 Pandas DataFrame objects or a DataFrame and a Series object on a common column (field). 

29. pandas.sort_values - sort_values() is used to sort column in a Pandas DataFrame (or a Pandas Series) by values in ascending or descending order. 

30. fillna - fillna() helps to replace all NaN values in a DataFrame or Series by imputing these missing values with more appropriate values.

31. pandas.rename :: RENAME SPECIFIC COLUMNS

32. pandas.map

33. pandas.apply

34. pandas.unique

35. pandas.crosstab

36. pandas.transpose()











